      <h3>Why One A Day Prenatal Is Our Top Pick</h3>

      <p>One A Day has been a trusted name in women's health for decades, and their prenatal gummy earns our top recommendation for one decisive reason: it is one of the only prenatal gummies that delivers DHA at the clinically recommended dose of 200mg per serving. Most prenatal gummies contain 50-60mg of DHA — a fraction of what is needed to support fetal brain and retinal development during the third trimester, when DHA accumulation accelerates dramatically.</p>

      <p>The formula also includes 800mcg of folic acid, exceeding ACOG's minimum recommendation of 600mcg to provide a safety margin. Iron is present as well, which is rare in gummy prenatals and critically important for the 45% increase in blood volume that occurs during pregnancy. Iron deficiency anemia during pregnancy is associated with preterm birth and low birth weight — risks that many gummy-only prenatal regimens fail to address.</p>

      <p>The 90-serving count provides a full three months of supplementation for $19.99, making this one of the most cost-effective prenatal gummies available at just $0.22 per serving. The one caveat: women who experience significant nausea may find the iron component aggravating during the first trimester. If that applies to you, consider switching to an iron-free option like Vitafusion during weeks 6-14 and returning to One A Day once nausea subsides.</p>

