      <h3>Vitafusion Prenatal: Best-Tasting Option for Morning Sickness</h3>

      <p>When morning sickness makes every supplement feel like a battle, taste becomes the most important factor in prenatal compliance. Vitafusion wins this category decisively. Their lemon and raspberry lemonade flavors are genuinely enjoyable — not medicinal, not cloying — and the soft texture goes down easily even when nausea is at its worst. With over 34,000 reviews averaging 4.6 stars, the consensus on taste is overwhelming.</p>

      <p>The formula delivers 800mcg of folic acid, adequate vitamin D3, and a solid B-complex. At $14.99 for 90 servings, Vitafusion is also the most affordable prenatal gummy on this list at just $0.17 per serving. For budget-conscious families, the savings add up — roughly $60 less per year compared to premium options like Ritual.</p>

      <p>The limitation is DHA. At 50mg per serving, Vitafusion delivers only 25% of the minimum recommended daily DHA intake for pregnant women. DHA is essential for fetal brain development, particularly during the third trimester when the fetal brain undergoes rapid growth. If you choose Vitafusion for its taste and affordability, <strong>you should add a separate DHA supplement</strong> (200-300mg daily) or ensure you are consuming 2-3 servings of low-mercury fish per week. The absence of iron is another gap that may require separate supplementation, especially in the second and third trimesters.</p>

