      <h3>SmartyPants Prenatal: The Nutrient-Dense Powerhouse</h3>

      <p>If your goal is to pack the maximum number of evidence-based nutrients into a prenatal gummy, SmartyPants has no equal. This is the only prenatal gummy on our list that includes methylfolate, omega-3 DHA and EPA, vitamin K2, vitamin D3, vitamin B12, iodine, and zinc in a single product. The ingredient list reads like a checklist of everything an OB-GYN would want in a prenatal supplement.</p>

      <p>The methylfolate decision is significant. Rather than using synthetic folic acid, SmartyPants uses 600mcg of methylfolate (5-MTHF) — the biologically active form of folate that bypasses the MTHFR conversion pathway entirely. For the estimated 40% of women who carry an MTHFR gene variant, this means more reliable folate delivery when it matters most. The 288mg of omega-3 fatty acids from sustainably sourced fish oil is also noteworthy, coming closer to the 200-300mg DHA target than any gummy except Ritual.</p>

      <p>The trade-offs are real. The fish oil component means SmartyPants is not vegan-friendly, and some women report a mild fishy aftertaste — particularly problematic during the first trimester when taste sensitivity is heightened. The $0.50 per serving price point also places this firmly in premium territory. For women who prioritize ingredient comprehensiveness and can tolerate fish-derived omega-3s, SmartyPants delivers exceptional nutritional coverage in gummy form.</p>

