      <h3>Nature Made Prenatal: USP-Verified Quality You Can Trust</h3>

      <p>In the supplement industry, third-party testing is the closest thing to a guarantee that what is on the label is actually in the bottle. Nature Made's USP Verification means that every batch has been independently tested for ingredient identity, potency, purity, and dissolution by the United States Pharmacopeia — a non-profit scientific organization established in 1820. <strong>Fewer than 1% of supplement brands carry USP Verification</strong>, and Nature Made is the only prenatal gummy on this list with this certification.</p>

      <p>For pregnant women, this matters enormously. When you are supplementing during a period where every nutrient delivery counts, you need to know that the 800mcg of folic acid on the label translates to 800mcg in the gummy. The formula also includes iodine (220mcg), which is critical for fetal thyroid development and often overlooked in prenatal supplements. The American Thyroid Association specifically recommends iodine supplementation during pregnancy and lactation.</p>

      <p>The shortcoming is the same as Vitafusion: low DHA at 60mg per serving. Nature Made also uses folic acid rather than methylfolate, which may be less optimal for MTHFR carriers. Despite these limitations, the USP Verification alone makes Nature Made a compelling choice for women who prioritize ingredient accuracy and purity above all else. Your OB-GYN's office likely stocks this brand in their sample closet — and there is a reason for that.</p>

